    "body": "<!-- Thank you for your contribution! We appreciate it. The following guidelines will help improve your pull request and facilitate feedback. If anything is unclear, don't hesitate to submit your pull request and ask the maintainers for assistance. -->\r\n\r\nCredits: @poyenc , @amd-hhashemi , @linsun12 , @tenpercent , @carlushuang , @HaiShaw \r\n\r\n## Motivation\r\n\r\nAdd ROCm custom attention backends to enable Flex Attn.\r\n\r\n## Modifications\r\n\r\n<!-- Describe the changes made in this PR. -->\r\n\r\n`--attention-backend aiter`: prefill: flashinfer-mod + decode: aiter decode (flex attn feasible)\r\n`--attention-backend aiter_decode`:  prefill: triton + decode: aiter decode\r\n\r\nROCm default backend: triton (no need to assign, flex attn infeasible)\r\n`--attention-backend triton`:  prefill: triton + decode: triton\r\n\r\n\r\n```\r\n/sgl-workspace/sglang# python -m sglang.bench_one_batch --batch-size 16 --input 1024 --output 256 --model /data/lmzheng-grok-1/ --tokenizer-path Xenova/grok-1-tokenizer --tp 8 --quantization fp8 --attention-backend aiter\r\nBenchmark ...\r\nPrefill. latency: 1.00044 s, throughput:  16376.85 token/s\r\nDecode.  latency: 0.01589 s, throughput:   1006.90 token/s\r\nDecode.  latency: 0.01767 s, throughput:    905.38 token/s\r\nDecode.  latency: 0.01731 s, throughput:    924.33 token/s\r\nDecode.  latency: 0.01712 s, throughput:    934.68 token/s\r\nDecode.  latency: 0.01736 s, throughput:    921.60 token/s\r\nDecode.  median latency: 0.02068 s, median throughput:    773.76 token/s\r\nTotal. latency:  6.204 s, throughput:   3301.17 token/s\r\n\r\n/sgl-workspace/sglang# python -m sglang.bench_one_batch --batch-size 16 --input 1024 --output 256 --model /data/lmzheng-grok-1/ --tokenizer-path Xenova/grok-1-tokenizer --tp 8 --quantization fp8 --attention-backend aiter_decode\r\nBenchmark ...\r\nPrefill. latency: 0.96845 s, throughput:  16917.67 token/s\r\nDecode.  latency: 0.01625 s, throughput:    984.46 token/s\r\nDecode.  latency: 0.01542 s, throughput:   1037.58 token/s\r\nDecode.  latency: 0.01520 s, throughput:   1052.54 token/s\r\nDecode.  latency: 0.01550 s, throughput:   1032.25 token/s\r\nDecode.  latency: 0.01575 s, throughput:   1016.12 token/s\r\nDecode.  median latency: 0.01882 s, median throughput:    849.98 token/s\r\nTotal. latency:  5.772 s, throughput:   3548.01 token/s\r\n\r\n/sgl-workspace/sglang# python -m sglang.bench_one_batch --batch-size 16 --input 1024 --output 256 --model /data/lmzheng-grok-1/ --tokenizer-path Xenova/grok-1-tokenizer --tp 8 --quantization fp8\r\nBenchmark ...\r\nPrefill. latency: 0.96759 s, throughput:  16932.75 token/s\r\nDecode.  latency: 0.01613 s, throughput:    991.91 token/s\r\nDecode.  latency: 0.01643 s, throughput:    973.75 token/s\r\nDecode.  latency: 0.01622 s, throughput:    986.20 token/s\r\nDecode.  latency: 0.01642 s, throughput:    974.51 token/s\r\nDecode.  latency: 0.01644 s, throughput:    973.37 token/s\r\nDecode.  median latency: 0.01974 s, median throughput:    810.42 token/s\r\nTotal. latency:  6.024 s, throughput:   3399.68 token/s\r\n```\r\n\r\n## TODO\r\nThis is enablement, performance improvements (prefill** , decode*) are in parallel.\r\n\r\n## Notes\r\nThis works around #4172 , moving AMD `flashinfer-mod` into base image.\r\n\r\n\r\n## Checklist\r\n\r\n- [ ] Format your code according to the [Code Formatting with Pre-Commit](https://docs.sglang.ai/references/contribution_guide.html#code-formatting-with-pre-commit).\r\n- [ ] Add unit tests as outlined in the [Running Unit Tests](https://docs.sglang.ai/references/contribution_guide.html#running-unit-tests-adding-to-ci).\r\n- [ ] Update documentation / docstrings / example tutorials as needed, according to [Writing Documentation](https://docs.sglang.ai/references/contribution_guide.html#writing-documentation-running-docs-ci).\r\n- [ ] Provide throughput / latency benchmark results and accuracy evaluation results as needed, according to [Benchmark and Profiling](https://docs.sglang.ai/references/benchmark_and_profiling.html) and [Accuracy Results](https://docs.sglang.ai/references/accuracy_evaluation.html).\r\n- [ ] For reviewers: If you haven't made any contributions to this PR and are only assisting with merging the main branch, please remove yourself as a co-author when merging the PR.\r\n- [ ] Please feel free to join our Slack channel at https://slack.sglang.ai to discuss your PR.\r\n",
